---
import PolicyBlock from '../PolicyBlock.astro';
import PolicySection from '../PolicySection.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<PolicyBlock
  id="terms-rolling-escape"
  title="Rolling Escape"
  badgeLabel="Terms & Conditions"
  updated="July 5, 2026"
>
  <PolicySection heading="Agreement">
    <p>By downloading, installing, or playing <strong>Rolling Escape</strong> you agree to be bound by these Terms and Conditions. If you do not agree, do not use the App.</p>
  </PolicySection>
  <PolicySection heading="License">
    <p>Ball Studios grants you a limited, personal, non-commercial, non-transferable, revocable license to use the App on Android devices you own or control, solely for your personal entertainment. You may not sublicense, sell, resell, or commercially exploit the App or its content in any way.</p>
  </PolicySection>
  <PolicySection heading="Virtual currency & rewarded ads">
    <p>The App does not offer real-money purchases. Coins are earned by playing — completing levels and scoring points — and are spent inside the App to unlock cosmetic ball skins and permanent gameplay power-ups (such as shields, extra lives, and a coin magnet). Some items can optionally be unlocked faster by watching a rewarded video ad via Google AdMob instead of spending coins. Ball Studios reserves the right to modify coin rewards, prices, or available items at any time without prior notice.</p>
  </PolicySection>
  <PolicySection heading="Virtual items">
    <p>Coins, skins, and power-ups in the App are virtual items with no monetary value outside the App. They cannot be transferred to other users, exchanged for real money, or redeemed for goods or services.</p>
  </PolicySection>
  <PolicySection heading="Advertising">
    <p>The App displays advertisements via Google AdMob, including optional rewarded video ads. Users in the EEA and UK will be asked for consent before personalized ads are shown. See our <a href={`${base}/privacy#privacy-rolling-escape`}>Privacy Policy</a> for details.</p>
  </PolicySection>
  <PolicySection heading="Intellectual property">
    <p>All content within the App — including graphics, code, sound, level design, and the Ball Studios name and logo — is the exclusive property of Ball Studios. You may not copy, modify, distribute, decompile, or create derivative works without express written permission.</p>
  </PolicySection>
  <PolicySection heading="Disclaimers">
    <p>The App is provided <em>"as is"</em> without warranties of any kind. Ball Studios does not warrant that the App will be error-free or uninterrupted. Your use of the App is at your sole risk.</p>
  </PolicySection>
  <PolicySection heading="Limitation of liability">
    <p>To the fullest extent permitted by law, Ball Studios shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of the App. Our total liability shall not exceed the amount you paid in in-app purchases in the three months preceding the claim.</p>
  </PolicySection>
  <PolicySection heading="Changes to terms">
    <p>We may update these Terms at any time. Changes will be posted on this page with a revised date. Continued use of the App after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance.</p>
  </PolicySection>
  <PolicySection heading="Governing law">
    <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of Colombia. Any disputes shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of Colombia.</p>
  </PolicySection>
  <PolicySection heading="Contact">
    <p>Questions about these Terms: <a href="mailto:lsalazarbedon@gmail.com">lsalazarbedon@gmail.com</a></p>
  </PolicySection>
</PolicyBlock>
